b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15042.htm)  [Next](sbe15044.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 64\n\n## THIRD VALL\xc3\x8e,\n\n## OR, THE CHAPTER OF BH _RI_ GU.\n\nHari _h_ , Om! May it (the Brahman) protect us both! May it enjoy us both! May\nwe acquire strength together! May our knowledge become bright! May we never\nquarrel! Peace! peace! peace 1!\n\n### FIRST ANUV\xc3\x82KA.\n\nBh _ri_ gu Varu _n_ i went to his father Varu _n_ a, saying:\n\nSir, teach me Brahman.' He told him this, viz. Food, breath, the eye, the ear,\nmind, speech.\n\nThen he said again to him: 'That from whence these beings are born, that by\nwhich, when born, they live, that into which they enter at their death, try to\nknow that. That is Brahman.'\n\nHe performed penance. Having performed penance--\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[64:1](sbe15043.htm#fr_235) The same paragraph, as before (II, 1), occurs at\nthe end of the Ka _th_ a-upanishad, and elsewhere.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 2](sbe15044.htm)\n\n"